Ubuntu, Nginx and PHP FPM Installation Steps

Update apt packages
-> apt update

Use apt package manager to install Nginx
-> apt install nginx -y

Use apt package manager to install Nano
-> apt install nano -y

Install Php FPM

	Install software-properties-common to be able to add PPA
	-> apt install software-properties-common -y

	Add PPA (Personal Package Archives)
	-> add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php -y

	Update apt packages
	-> apt update

	Install PHP FPM
	-> apt install php7.2 php7.2-common php7.2-cli php7.2-fpm -y

Enable PHP FPM on Nginx

Copy app file to nginx /etc/nginx/sites-enabled

Create a index.php file in /var/www/html

Restart Nginx
-> service nginx restart

Restart PHP FPM
-> service php7.2-fpm restart

HOW TO SET TIMEZONE WITHOUT INTERACTION:

	#!/bin/bash
	export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

	ln -fs /usr/share/zoneinfo/America/New_York /etc/localtime
	apt-get install -y tzdata
	dpkg-reconfigure --frontend noninteractive tzdata



